text: For those of you bashing the name of the movie. They did not pick it to bandwagon off of fame from the comic book character. First of all a Nightcrawler movie is completely improbable as Fox owns the rights and are pre occupied with X-Men Apocalypse. Second of all, the name "Nightcrawler" pertaining to a news crew is a group of people who report and film throughout the night to capitalize on the gruesome and horrific incidents that occur. They aren't that popular with the law as what they do is technically illegal which is why no one hears about them.
author: James Caddick

text: Some people get annoyed at the most innocuous things. Judging by the comments, you'd think "nightcrawler" was a word invented by Marvel. text: I hate COMIC BOOK FANBOYS so much, except for at the box office, where else do they matter?  No where, actual comic book sales are plummeting further than your local newspaper and they had wild expectations that graphic novels would propel their art into the realm of respectability.  It did not do so.  Comic book characters are fun for kids aged 8-14 (that's it) Chris Nolan packed a fairly entertaining and original comic book movie into the middle of an otherwise sub par trilogy - and Tim Burton made Batman visually entertaining as did Warren Beaty with Dick Tracy that's it - those three examples were the height of Comic book genius.    Scott Pilgrim, Ghost World, American Splendor, and Kick Ass served more as scripts for what turned to be decent movie but no way are FAN BOYS going to put those examples as how good Comic Books cause they really aren't.  Simply put Fan Boys are clinging on to Wolverine, Magneto, Superman, Batman, Fantastic Four, Spiderman, Iron man, Aquaman and Roger Rabbit for their hope that a comic book character might become a movie character that wins an Oscar.  Nobody cares about Comic Books, it's trendy, yes, but the trend is about to go BYE BYE

text: Saw this last night, it is very good. Lean and very slick but with real satire of media, news and the job market but most of all people's ambition. Lou is reminiscent of Rupert Pupkin (De Niro's greatest performance) and the film has a lot of elements of films like Network. People will come away from this saying "Lou is such a crazy nasty guy" which is true in a way but what is truly scary about him is that he is the successful/ambition/follow your dream self help type shit personified, which people eat up in america. He is actually the american dream in a way - builds his way up the chain at all costs with little or no regard for others, so long as he gains success.

author: Nate Reyes

text: With a slim few exceptions (which actually includes several x men films, one of the more nuanced and interesting comic franchises), superhero movies are not only trashy, but harmful to society and hinting of fascism. The fact that so many people (a disturbing number of which are actually NOT morons) support and legitimately enjoy them is troubling to me.     Media is powerful and popular films do have an effect on our lives as people tend to emulate what they see and absorb the lessons inherent in storytelling. Maybe we have a spoiled rich wannabe dictator in the white house because so many people in America have been worshiping billionaires who beat up street criminals and "heroes" who possess incredible power they didn't have to earn.     And as far as the title goes, "nightcrawler" is a slang term for news stringers; the profession that Gyllenhaal's character holds in the film. And if you didn't watch it because there are no flying robots, you missed out on one of the best films of the decade, far more interesting and thought provoking than whatever dull business the avengers are  up to.     But it's not too late!! you can correct this grievous error and treat yourself to a thrilling critique of modern day capitalism and the behavior it encourages. Hooray for cinema!
